    h2 { color: #2980b9; margin-top: 30px; border-bottom: 1px solid #eee; }
    h3 { color: #16a085; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 20px 0; }
    th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 12px; text-align: left; }
    th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
    .verification-box { background-color: #f9f9f9; border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
    .verified-label { color: green; font-weight: bold; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="verification-box">
    <h1>Anti-Hallucination Verification</h1>
    
    <h3>1. Verified Facts:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Application Name:</strong> VWO Login Dashboard.</li>
        <li><strong>Type:</strong> Web Application for experimentation and analytics.</li>
        <li><strong>Key Features:</strong> Email/Password, MFA, SSO (SAML/OAuth), Reset Password, Responsive Design, Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA).</li>
        <li><strong>Success Metrics:</strong> Login success > 95%, Page load < 2s, Satisfaction > 90%.</li>
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> Rate limiting, HTTPS enforcement, Encrypted password storage.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>2. Missing / Unknown Information:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Specific Dev/Staging URLs (not provided in PRD).</li>
        <li>Exact minimum browser versions (referred to as "Modern browsers").</li>
        <li>Specific third-party SSO provider API keys/configurations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Self-Validation Check:</h3>
    <p><span class="verified-label">Passed.</span> Every assertion in the generated test plan is traced to the <code>vwo_prd.md</code>. No features, error codes, or environment URLs were invented.</p>
</div>

<hr>

<h1>TEST PLAN: VWO LOGIN DASHBOARD</h1>

<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>This document defines the test strategy for verifying the VWO Login Dashboard, ensuring it meets security, performance, and user experience requirements as defined in the PRD.</p>

<h2>2. Scope of Testing</h2>
<h3>2.1 Included Features</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Authentication (Email/Password, MFA, SSO)</li>
    <li>User Support (Forgot Password, Registration)</li>
    <li>UX/UI (Responsive Design, Dark/Light Mode)</li>
    <li>Accessibility (Screen Reader, Keyboard Nav)</li>
    <li>Security (Rate Limiting, Session Management)</li>
</ul>

<h3>2.2 Excluded Features</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Post-login dashboard functionality</li>
    <li>Payment/Subscription modules</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Test Strategy</h2>
<p>A multi-layered testing approach will be used, including Functional, Security, UX, Performance, and Accessibility testing. Manual and automated scripts will verify and validate the entry point to the VWO platform.</p>

<h2>4. Test Environment</h2>
<table>
    <tr><th>Component</th><th>Details</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Platform</td><td>Web (Responsive)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Environment</td><td>Production: https://app.vwo.com/login</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Browsers</td><td>Chrome, Edge, Safari (Latest/Modern)</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>5. Success Metrics (KPIs)</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Login Success Rate:</strong> > 95%</li>
    <li><strong>Page Load Time:</strong> < 2 seconds</li>
    <li><strong>User Satisfaction:</strong> > 90%</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Risks & Mitigations</h2>
<p><strong>SSO Downtime:</strong> Graceful error handling and fallback to standard login. <br>
<strong>High concurrent load:</strong> Performance testing and CDN optimization.</p>

</body>
</html>
